## Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

This is a textbook case of **coverage-touching** — every production method is called (achieving line coverage) but almost nothing is actually verified. These tests would still pass if you replaced every method body with `{ }`.

---

### 🔴 CRITICAL — Assertion-Free Tests (Coverage Without Verification)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | `AddProduct_Works` | **Zero assertions.** Proves nothing. |
| 2 | `UpdatePrice_Works` | **Zero assertions.** Price change is never checked. |
| 3 | `RemoveProduct_Works` | **Zero assertions.** Product could still exist. |
| 4 | `GetProductCount_Works` | **Zero assertions.** Count result is discarded. |
| 5 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | **Zero assertions.** Discount could be wrong or no-op. |
| 6 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` | **Zero assertions.** Import could silently corrupt data. |

**Fix pattern** — verify the *observable side-effect*:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProductRetrievableBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", result!.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, result.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_MakesProductUnretrievable()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}

[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_ReducesAllPrices()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 100m));
    _catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

    Assert.AreEqual(90m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
}
```

---

### 🟠 HIGH — Shallow/Trivial Assertions (Only `IsNotNull`)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 7 | `GetProduct_Works` | Asserts non-null but never checks SKU, Name, or Price. |
| 8 | `SearchProducts_Works` | Asserts list is non-null but not that it contains the correct item or has the right count. |
| 9 | `GetAllProducts_Works` | Same — non-null check on a `List<T>` (which is never null from `ToList()`). |
| 10 | `ExportToCsv_Works` | Asserts CSV string is non-null, never validates content. |

**Fix pattern** — assert on *values and cardinality*:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetProduct_ReturnsCorrectProduct()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");

    Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001", result!.Sku);
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", result.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, result.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void Search_ReturnsOnlyMatchingProducts()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));

    var results = _catalog.Search("Widget");

    Assert.AreEqual(1, results.Count);
    Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001", results[0].Sku);
}

[TestMethod]
public void ExportToCsv_ProducesCorrectFormat()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99));
    var csv = _catalog.ExportToCsv();

    Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001,Widget,9.99", csv);
}
```

