### Summary

| Severity | Count | Pattern |
|----------|-------|---------|
| 🔴 Critical | 6 | Assertion-free (coverage-touching) |
| 🟠 High | 4 | Trivial `IsNotNull` on non-nullable returns |
| 🟡 Medium | 5+ | Missing negative/boundary tests |

**Root cause:** Every test follows the same template — call the method, maybe assign the return value, never verify outcomes. This inflates coverage metrics while providing near-zero defect detection. The 95% coverage number is illusory.
